Package: minervadb-server
Version: 24.12.1-1
Architecture: all
Maintainer: MinervaDB Engineering <engineering@minervadb.xyz>
Installed-Size: 2048
Depends: clickhouse-server (>= 24.1), clickhouse-client (>= 24.1), curl, ca-certificates, openssl
Recommends: clickhouse-keeper (>= 24.1)
Section: database
Priority: optional
Homepage: https://github.com/MinervaDB/MinervaDB-Server
Description: MinervaDB Server for ClickHouse -- Enterprise-grade ClickHouse distribution
 MinervaDB Server for ClickHouse is an enterprise-grade distribution and
 configuration overlay for ClickHouse -- the world's fastest open-source
 real-time analytics database -- enhanced with curated extensions,
 operational tooling, and comprehensive documentation.
 .
 This package installs:
  * Production-hardened config.d / users.d XML overlays into
    /etc/clickhouse-server/
  * Full MinervaDB source tree under /opt/minervadb-server
  * Helper scripts for backup, diagnostics, and upgrades
 .
 Coverage areas:
  * Performance Engineering (MergeTree tuning, query optimisation, I/O)
  * Scalability (horizontal sharding, vertical sizing, cloud-native)
  * Observability & Monitoring (Prometheus, Grafana, OpenTelemetry)
  * Troubleshooting (runbooks for every common failure mode)
  * Disaster Recovery (clickhouse-backup, S3/GCS/Azure, PITR)
  * High Availability (ClickHouse Keeper, HAProxy, rolling upgrades)
 .
 After installation restart ClickHouse:
  systemctl restart clickhouse-server
